Related external libraries    {#externaldocs}
==========================

From [LCG version @LCG_VERSION@][lcg-details]:

## Required Dependencies

- **Core Libraries:**
  - [ROOT @ROOT_config_version@][root] (persistency, histogramming, I/O)
  - [Boost @Boost_version@](http://www.boost.org/doc/libs/@Boost_url_version@/) (filesystem, regex, fiber, thread, python, unit_test_framework, program_options, log, log_setup, graph)
  - [Python @Python_config_version@](http://www.python.org/doc/@Python_config_version@/) (scripting and interactivity)
  - [TBB @TBB_config_version@](https://www.threadingbuildingblocks.org/) (threading building blocks)

- **System Libraries:**
  - UUID (universally unique identifier)
  - Threads (POSIX threads)
  - ZLIB @ZLIB_config_version@ (compression)
  - Rangev3 (C++ ranges library)
  - cppgsl (C++ Guidelines Support Library)
  - fmt (formatting library)
  - nlohmann_json (JSON library)

## Optional Dependencies

- **Histogramming:**
  - [AIDA @AIDA_config_version@](http://aida.freehep.org/doc/v@AIDA_config_version@/api/) (Abstract Interfaces for Data Analysis)

- **XML Processing:**
  - [Xerces-C @XercesC_config_version@](http://xml.apache.org/xerces-c/api-@XercesC_major_version@)

- **Physics Libraries:**
  - [CLHEP @CLHEP_config_version@](http://proj-clhep.web.cern.ch/proj-clhep/) (C++ Class Library for High Energy Physics)
  - [HepPDT @HepPDT_config_version@](http://lcgapp.cern.ch/project/simu/HepPDT/) (Particle Data Table)

- **Testing:**
  - [Catch2 @Catch2_config_version@](https://github.com/catchorg/Catch2) (modern C++ testing framework)
  - [CppUnit @CppUnit_config_version@](https://freedesktop.org/wiki/Software/cppunit/) (unit testing framework)
  - Boost unit_test_framework (part of Boost libraries)

- **Documentation:**
  - [Doxygen @Doxygen_config_version@](https://www.doxygen.nl/) (documentation generation)

- **GPU Computing:**
  - [CUDA](https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-toolkit) (when GAUDI_USE_CUDA is enabled)

## Platform-Specific Dependencies

- **Linux:**
  - rt (real-time library)

- **macOS:**
  - Foundation (Core Foundation framework)


